## Choosing a Cloud Provider

### Comparison Table

| Feature | iCloud Drive | Google Drive | OneDrive | Proton Drive | Dropbox |
|---------|--------------|--------------|----------|--------------|---------|
| **Free Storage** | 5GB | 15GB | 5GB | 1GB (E2EE) | 2GB |
| **Desktop App** | macOS built-in, Windows app | Yes | Windows built-in, macOS app | Yes | Yes |
| **Platforms** | macOS, iOS, Windows | All | All | All | All |
| **Real-time Sync** | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes |
| **Encryption** | In transit + at rest | In transit + at rest | In transit + at rest | End-to-end | In transit + at rest |
| **Best For** | Apple users | Most storage | Windows users | Privacy | Reliability |
| **Paid Plans** | $0.99/mo (50GB) | $1.99/mo (100GB) | $1.99/mo (100GB) | $3.99/mo (200GB) | $9.99/mo (2TB) |

### Recommendations

**For most users:** **Google Drive** (15GB free, works everywhere)

**For Apple users:** **iCloud Drive** (seamless across Mac/iPhone/iPad)

**For Windows users:** **OneDrive** (built-in, no extra app needed)

**For privacy-focused users:** **Proton Drive** (end-to-end encrypted)

**For reliability:** **Dropbox** (been around longest, very stable)

